#  Credit Card Fraud Detection System

A Machine Learning-based Credit Card Fraud Detection System that identifies fraudulent transactions using the European Credit Card Fraud Dataset. The project compares multiple machine learning algorithms 

---


##  Dataset

**Dataset:** European Credit Card Fraud Detection Dataset

https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mlg-ulb/creditcardfraud


---

##  Tech Stack

### Machine Learning
- Python
- Scikit-learn
- Pandas
- NumPy


---

##  Models Implemented

- Logistic Regression (Baseline)
- Random Forest Classifier
- XGBoost Classifier

The best-performing model was selected based on fraud detection metrics.

---

##  Model Performance

| Metric | Score |
|---------|------:|
| Test Accuracy | **99.95%** |
| Fraud Precision | **91%** |
| Fraud Recall | **81%** |
| Fraud F1-Score | **0.85** |
| Macro F1-Score | **0.93** |

---

##  Key Achievements

- Achieved **99.95% test accuracy** on the European Credit Card Fraud Dataset.
- Detected **81% of fraudulent transactions** with **91% precision**.
- Compared Logistic Regression, Random Forest, and XGBoost to identify the best-performing model.

